Title: Nerdcore is Dead(?)
Presenters: YTCracker, Steffo, StarF, King Pheenix, 2 Mello, Devo Spice
Book Description: 'Nerdcore hip-hop is often taken as a parody genre.  With 'nerdy' references sneaking into more and more mainstream music- is 'nerd rap' a stale term?  Join some of the top artists as they debate the validity of their own genre.'

Title: Performance: King Pheenix
Book Description: 'King Pheenix (Scott Shepley) has been a recording artist since 2003.  After releasing his Third album- Event Horizon:No Turning back. and with many projects in the cache for 2014… many people are asking – is the Pheenix ready to re-gen? Check out his hip hop with a nerdy twinge. '

Title: After Hours Panel: Scrubcast Live!
Book Description: 'What does a hurricane of comedy mixed with a tornado of entertainment sound like? If you said a stupid analogy- you are right. Scrubcast alumni King Pheenix- StarF- and 2 Mello- will rock your face off with laughter. With their own style of drunken riffing and random observation- this will be a night that you would regret missing.'

Title: Scrub Club Records Presents: DIY Till I Die: How to be a Successful Independent Artist
Book Description: 'Scrub Club Records is the world's first and only- not for profit- independent- open source music label. Many people have questions on what it takes to be successful independently- and we are here to help! King Pheenix- StarF and 2 Mello will take your questions- and give you answers ranging from inspirational- to possibly insane- but always entertaining. Music is love -- let's spread it.'
